A Five Minute Ride In A Police Chopper By Vincent Musila Is An Adventure He Had Waited For, For Many Years. But Due To The Heavy Rains, It Turned Out To Be More Than He Had Bargained For. It Took The Intervention Of Police Officers To Rescue Him After He Was Marooned For Three Days And Nights At The Fourteen Falls In Thika. The Young Man Was Airlifted On A National Police Service Helicopter Yesterday Evening From The Flooded River Athi In Kiambu County As Relieved Villagers Cheered On. Musila, A Fisherman Had Gone To Lay His Fishing Nets On A Section Of The River Using His Canoe That Fateful Evening At Around 9 Pm.